Class PlayerChoicesDataStructure

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.is25am33.model.card.PlayerChoicesDataStructure
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class PlayerChoicesDataStructure extends Object implements Serializable
This class represents a structured collection of player-selected options used to communicate the player's decisions to the gameModel model. It encapsulates all possible choices made by the user during various phases of gameplay, including component selections, planet visits, and reward acceptance.

The contained choices are utilized by the model to process and execute player actions accordingly.
